The paper discusses the use of machine learning (ML) for solving combinatorial optimization problems, specifically the Travelling Salesman Problem (TSP). This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to ML and optimization. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of deep (reinforcement) learning for solving the TSP. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper focuses on evaluating ML approaches for combinatorial optimization. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses algorithms for solving the TSP. 

cs.RO (Robotics) is less likely but still possible as the TSP is a problem that arises in robotics and the paper discusses the use of a search procedure plugged inside a ML model. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper discusses the use of deep learning for solving the TSP.
